    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine domini nostri Iesu Christi Dei eterni. <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/21">Berengarius </persName>divina
                        favente clemencia <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>. Si regalis providencia
                        divino inflammata amore sacratis locis libenter exhibere contendit, procul
                        dubio gloriam eterne possessionis promerebitur et divinis aminiculis regnum
                        euis fulciri non ambigitur. Quapropter omnium fidelium sancte Dei Ecclesie
                        nostrorumque presentium scilicet et futurorum noverit solercia, <persName
                            key="#Archbishops #Patriarchs" ref="#people/153">Fredericum</persName>
                        reverentisiimum <rs key="#Archbishops #Patriarchs"> patriarcham</rs>,
                        nostrum videlicet spiritalem patrem, nostram humillime adiisse mansuetudinem
                        postulando, quatenus ob divinum intuitum et nostrae anime remedium
                        parentumque nostrorum et aucmentacionem nostre prolis nec non et nostri
                        regni stabilimentum quandam aquam nomine <rs
                            key="#Rivers #Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Natissum</rs>, que inferius <placeName
                            key="#Rivers #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Canals"
                            ref="#places/162"><rs key="#Rivers #Canals">Anfora</rs></placeName>
                        cognominatur <orgName
                            key="#Rivers #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Fisheries #Mills #Fiscal_property #Other_administrative_unit #Census #Profits_of_justice #Churches #Abbots"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/92">sanctae Aquilegensi </orgName><rs
                            key="#Churches">eclesiae</rs> perpetuis temporibus habendam <rs
                            key="#Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure">iure proprietario</rs> concedere
                        dignaremur. Cuius iustis precibus animum nostre benivolentie de more
                        flectentes, pretaxam aquam hactenus pertinentem <geogName
                            key="#Rivers #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Sea #Fisheries #Mills #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Canals #Other_administrative_unit #Census"
                            >de <rs
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Gastaldus/vicegastaldus #Other_administrative_unit"
                                >gastaldato </rs><placeName
                                key="#Rivers #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Fisheries #Mills #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Canals #Gastaldus/vicegastaldus #Other_administrative_unit #Census"
                                >Anpliano</placeName></geogName> penitus terminantem in <rs
                            key="#Sea">mari</rs> simul cum suis <rs
                            key="#Fisheries #Allocation_to_churches">piscationibus</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Mills"
                            >molendinis</rs>, et <rs
                            key="#Marshes/lagoons/tombolos"
                            >palud(ibus)</rs> et <rs key="#Census">censum</rs> qui annualiter nostre
                        partis dabatur cum omni integritate, <rs key="#Profits_of_justice"
                            >placitum</rs> quoque prefati negocii prescripte eclesis Aquilegensi
                        con√ßedimus et perdonamus, quatenus idem reverentissimus patriarcha vel qui
                        pro tempore in predicta sede ordinati fuerint habeant, teneant, possideant
                        et ordinent ecclesiastico iure, prout eis melius visum fuerit santientes, ut
                        nullus dux, comes, gastaldius, aut quislibet rei publice exactor contra hanc
                        nostra dapsilitatis auctoritatem insurgere conetur, sed liceat eidem
                        religioso patriarche vel his qui pro tempore fuerint pro nostris inconvulsis
                        beneficis salutiferas orationes pro nostre tuitionis sal[vati]one et nostre
                        prolis aucmentacione ad Deum inces[santer orationes] effundere. Si quis vero
                        contra hanc nostram regalem institucionem [ac perdo]nationem insurgere
                        temptaverit, sciat se compositurum <rs key="#Penalty">auri obrizi libras
                            sexaginta</rs>, medietatem <rs key="#Camera_regis">camere nostre</rs> et
                        medietatem sepe nominate sanctae Aquilegensi eclesie eiusque pontificibus
                        qui pro tempore ibi ordinati fuerint. Et ut hoc verius credatur
                        diligentiusque ab omnibus observetur, manu propria confirmatum de anulo
                        nostro subter iussimus insigniri. Signum domni (M) Berengarii gloriosissimi
                        regis. <persName key="#Chancellor"><name ref="Beatus"
                            >Beatus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> ad vicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor"><name ref="Liutwardus">Liutardi</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Archchancellor">archicancellarii</rs> recognovi [et subscripsi].
                        Data .III. id. novemb., anno incarnationis domini nostri Iesu Christi
                        .DCCCC., anno vero regni domni Berengarii regis .XIII. per indictionem .III.
                        Actum <placeName ref="#places/158"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Function #Residential"
                                ><rs
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Function #Residential"
                                >Trieste</rs></placeName>. in Dei nomine feliciter, amen. </ab>
